{"session_id":"75e45cbf-59b8-4396-b32b-f2b7eb9eb296","transcript_path":"/home/blgroce/.claude/projects/-home-blgroce-tools-cli-tools/75e45cbf-59b8-4396-b32b-f2b7eb9eb296.jsonl","cwd":"/home/blgroce/tools/cli-tools","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","tool_name":"Edit","tool_input":{"file_path":"/home/blgroce/tools/cli-tools/CLAUDE.md","old_string":"# CLI Tools\nThe purpose of this entire project is to build cli tools that other agents will call.\n\n## RULES\n- Keep the scope simple but expandable. After planning or creating, always ask yourself \"Can I get the same outcome in a simpler way?\"","new_string":"# CLI Tools\nThe purpose of this entire project is to build cli tools that other agents will call.\n\n## RULES\n- Keep the scope simple but expandable. After planning or creating, always ask yourself \"Can I get the same outcome in a simpler way?\"\n\n---\n\n## Language & Framework\n- **Python** with **Typer** (or Click) for CLI framework\n- Typer is preferred - cleaner syntax, auto-generates `--help`\n\n## Installation\n- Installable via `pip install .` or `pipx install .`\n- Uses `pyproject.toml` with entry points\n- Each tool becomes a command: `mytool <subcommand>` or standalone `toolname`\n\n## Output Rules\n| Rule | Rationale |\n|------|-----------|\n| JSON to stdout by default | Agents parse it reliably |\n| Errors to stderr | Keeps stdout clean for piping |\n| No interactive prompts | Agents can't respond to \"Are you sure?\" |\n| `--format text` option for humans | Optional override |\n\n## Standard Flags (all tools)\n```\n--help, -h       Show help\n--version        Show version\n--quiet, -q      Suppress non-error output\n--format         json (default) | text\n```\n\n## Exit Codes\n```\n0 = Success\n1 = General error\n2 = Invalid arguments\n3 = Resource not found\n4 = External failure (API, network)\n```\n\n## Error Output Format\n```json\n{\"error\": true, \"code\": \"INVALID_INPUT\", \"message\": \"Expected file path\"}\n```\n\n## Success Output Format\n```json\n{\"success\": true, \"data\": { ... }}\n```\n\n## Project Structure\n```\ncli-tools/\n├── pyproject.toml          # Entry points for all tools\n├── src/\n│   ├── shared/             # Common utilities (errors, output formatting)\n│   └── tools/\n│       ├── tool_one/\n│       │   └── main.py\n│       └── tool_two/\n│           └── main.py\n└── tests/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions (to be decided)\n- **Single command with subcommands** (`agenttools scan`, `agenttools summarize`) or **separate binaries** (`agent-scan`, `agent-summarize`)?\n- **Naming convention** - prefix like `agent-*` or `at-*` or no prefix?","replace_all":false},"tool_response":{"filePath":"/home/blgroce/tools/cli-tools/CLAUDE.md","oldString":"# CLI Tools\nThe purpose of this entire project is to build cli tools that other agents will call.\n\n## RULES\n- Keep the scope simple but expandable. After planning or creating, always ask yourself \"Can I get the same outcome in a simpler way?\"","newString":"# CLI Tools\nThe purpose of this entire project is to build cli tools that other agents will call.\n\n## RULES\n- Keep the scope simple but expandable. After planning or creating, always ask yourself \"Can I get the same outcome in a simpler way?\"\n\n---\n\n## Language & Framework\n- **Python** with **Typer** (or Click) for CLI framework\n- Typer is preferred - cleaner syntax, auto-generates `--help`\n\n## Installation\n- Installable via `pip install .` or `pipx install .`\n- Uses `pyproject.toml` with entry points\n- Each tool becomes a command: `mytool <subcommand>` or standalone `toolname`\n\n## Output Rules\n| Rule | Rationale |\n|------|-----------|\n| JSON to stdout by default | Agents parse it reliably |\n| Errors to stderr | Keeps stdout clean for piping |\n| No interactive prompts | Agents can't respond to \"Are you sure?\" |\n| `--format text` option for humans | Optional override |\n\n## Standard Flags (all tools)\n```\n--help, -h       Show help\n--version        Show version\n--quiet, -q      Suppress non-error output\n--format         json (default) | text\n```\n\n## Exit Codes\n```\n0 = Success\n1 = General error\n2 = Invalid arguments\n3 = Resource not found\n4 = External failure (API, network)\n```\n\n## Error Output Format\n```json\n{\"error\": true, \"code\": \"INVALID_INPUT\", \"message\": \"Expected file path\"}\n```\n\n## Success Output Format\n```json\n{\"success\": true, \"data\": { ... }}\n```\n\n## Project Structure\n```\ncli-tools/\n├── pyproject.toml          # Entry points for all tools\n├── src/\n│   ├── shared/             # Common utilities (errors, output formatting)\n│   └── tools/\n│       ├── tool_one/\n│       │   └── main.py\n│       └── tool_two/\n│           └── main.py\n└── tests/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions (to be decided)\n- **Single command with subcommands** (`agenttools scan`, `agenttools summarize`) or **separate binaries** (`agent-scan`, `agent-summarize`)?\n- **Naming convention** - prefix like `agent-*` or `at-*` or no prefix?","originalFile":"# CLI Tools\nThe purpose of this entire project is to build cli tools that other agents will call.\n\n## RULES\n- Keep the scope simple but expandable. After planning or creating, always ask yourself \"Can I get the same outcome in a simpler way?\"","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":2,"oldLines":4,"newStart":2,"newLines":70,"lines":[" The purpose of this entire project is to build cli tools that other agents will call."," "," ## RULES","-- Keep the scope simple but expandable. After planning or creating, always ask yourself \"Can I get the same outcome in a simpler way?\"","\\ No newline at end of file","+- Keep the scope simple but expandable. After planning or creating, always ask yourself \"Can I get the same outcome in a simpler way?\"","+","+---","+","+## Language & Framework","+- **Python** with **Typer** (or Click) for CLI framework","+- Typer is preferred - cleaner syntax, auto-generates `--help`","+","+## Instal