l for description, and outputs/saves the description. Follows the same architecture as image-creator: Typer CLI, JSON output by default, standard flags (--help, --version, --quiet, --format), proper exit codes, and auth management via keyring/env var.\\\",\\n    \\\"started_at\\\": \\\"2026-02-09 15:28:06\\\",\\n    \\\"completed_at\\\": null,\\n    \\\"status\\\": \\\"running\\\",\\n    \\\"total_tasks\\\": 6,\\n    \\\"pending_tasks\\\": 3\\n  }\\n}\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"interrupted\":false,\"isImage\":false},\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01CgZiRStx9t3SLmFuGtvAEj\"}\n+---\n+[2026-02-09 09:38:56] RAW INPUT:\n+{\"session_id\":\"1c043b7a-e5d9-4745-9a9f-a4658d159e88\",\"transcript_path\":\"/home/blgroce/.claude/projects/-home-blgroce-tools-cli-tools/1c043b7a-e5d9-4745-9a9f-a4658d159e88.jsonl\",\"cwd\":\"/home/blgroce/tools/cli-tools\",\"permission_mode\":\"bypassPermissions\",\"hook_event_name\":\"PostToolUse\",\"tool_name\":\"Bash\",\"tool_input\":{\"command\":\"python3 .claude/skills/project-context/scripts/task_list.py --run-id 1 --pending\",\"description\":\"Get pending tasks for run 1\"},\"tool_response\":{\"stdout\":\"{\\n  \\\"tasks\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"id\\\": 4,\\n      \\\"run_id\\\": 1,\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"feature\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Implement describe command to send image to OpenRouter\\\",\\n      \\\"steps\\\": \\\"1. Add 'describe' command that takes image path as argument\\\\n2. Validate image file exists and is readable\\\\n3. Read image file and base64 encode it\\\\n4. Detect MIME type from file extension (jpg/jpeg/png/gif/webp)\\\\n5. Build OpenRouter API request with model, image as base64 data URL in content array\\\\n6. Send POST request to OpenRouter with Bearer token auth\\\\n7. Parse response and extract description text from choices[0].message.content\\\\n8. Add --model option to override default (e.g. --model google/gemini-2.5-pro-preview for higher quality)\\\\n9. Add --prompt option to customize the description prompt (default: 'Describe this image in detail')\\\",\\n      \\\"passes\\\": 0,\\n      \\\"status\\\": \\\"pending\\\",\\n      \\\"failure_reason\\\": null\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"id\\\": 5,\\n      \\\"run_id\\\": 1,\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"feature\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Add output saving functionality\\\",\\n      \\\"steps\\\": \\\"1. Add --out/-o option to describe command for output file path\\\\n2. If --out provided, write description text to that file\\\\n3. If --out is a directory, generate filename like description-YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS.txt\\\\n4. Create parent directories if they don't exist\\\\n5. Include save path in JSON success output when saving\\\\n6. Success output format: {success: true, data: {description: '...', image_path: '...', model: '...', saved_to: '...' (if applicable)}}\\\",\\n      \\\"passes\\\": 0,\\n      \\\"status\\\": \\\"pending\\\",\\n      \\\"failure_reason\\\": null\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"id\\\": 6,\\n      \\\"run_id\\\": 1,\\n      \\\"category\\\": \\\"feature\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Test and verify describe-image tool works end-to-end\\\",\\n      \\\"steps\\\": \\\"1. Install the package: cd describe-image && pip install -e .\\\\n2. Verify describe-image --help shows correct usage\\\\n3. Verify describe-image --version shows version\\\\n4. Test describe-image auth status\\\\n5. Test describe-image describe with a sample image (use an existing image or create a simple test image)\\\\n6. Verify JSON output format matches spec\\\\n7. Test --format text output\\\\n8. Test --out option saves description to file\\\\n9. Fix any issues found during testing\\\",\\n      \\\"passes\\\": 0,\\n      \\\"status\\\": \\\"pending\\\",\\n      \\\"failure_reason\\\": null\\n    }\\n  ],\\n  \\\"count\\\": 3\\n}\",\"stderr\":\"\",\"interrupted\":false,\"isImage\":false},\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01NSK2FuduCjTE15x248HkgX\"}\n+---\n+[2026-02-09 09:39:00] RAW INPUT:\n+{\"session_id\":\"1c043b7a-e5d9-4