**Custom ExitCode enum** (IntEnum):\n  - 0 = SUCCESS\n  - 1 = GENERAL_ERROR\n  - 2 = INVALID_ARGS\n  - 3 = NOT_FOUND\n  - 4 = EXTERNAL_FAILURE\n- `emit_error()` function handles all error output with:\n  - Appropriate HTTP-like code names (NOT_FOUND, INVALID_ARGS, EXTERNAL_FAILURE)\n  - Contextual exit code mapping\n  - Format-aware output (JSON or text)\n- Errors go to **stderr** (file=sys.stderr)\n- Success output goes to **stdout**\n\n### Standard Flags (Global Callback Pattern)\n```python\n--format (json|text)    # Output format\n--quiet, -q             # Suppress output\n--version               # Version info with eager callback\n```\n\n### CLI Structure\n- Uses **Typer** framework with `typer.Typer()` apps\n- **Subcommands via app.add_typer()** (e.g., auth_app for auth set/status/clear)\n- **OutputSettings dataclass** to pass format/quiet through context (`ctx.obj`)\n- **Global callback** (@app.callback()) validates format and sets context\n- `get_settings(ctx)` helper retrieves OutputSettings from context\n\n### Testing Patterns\n- **pytest** with **typer.testing.CliRunner** for CLI testing\n- **Fixtures** for common test data (runner, test_image, mock responses)\n- **unittest.mock** for mocking external API calls (requests.post, resolve_api_key)\n- **tempfile** for isolated file I/O testing\n- Tests check both exit code and parsed JSON output\n- Tests verify side effects (file creation, directory creation)\n\n### Key Implementation Details\n- All commands use `settings = get_settings(ctx)` to access format/quiet\n- Both success and error paths use helper functions: `emit_success()` and `emit_error()`\n- Version callback uses `is_eager=True` for early exit\n- Context object pattern (`ctx.obj = OutputSettings(...)`) passes settings to subcommands\n- No interactive prompts anywhere (agents can't respond)"}],"totalDurationMs":13675,"totalTokens":20385,"totalToolUseCount":5,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2161,"cache_read_input_tokens":175