\",\n      \"passes\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"pending\",\n      \"failure_reason\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"run_id\": 2,\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"Build company commands: add, list, show, edit, rm\",\n      \"steps\": \"1. Create crm/src/crm/commands/company.py with typer app\\n2. Implement 'add' command:\\n   - Args: name (required), --status, --industry, --website, --notes\\n   - Insert into companies table, emit success with company data\\n   - Handle duplicate name (unique constraint) with proper error\\n3. Implement 'list' command:\\n   - Optional --status filter\\n   - Return array of companies as JSON\\n   - Text format: rich table with columns: ID, Name, Industry, Status\\n4. Implement 'show' command:\\n   - Arg: name (required), look up by name\\n   - Include related contacts count and deals count in output\\n   - Error if not found (exit code 3)\\n5. Implement 'edit' command:\\n   - Arg: name (required), optional --name, --status, --industry, --website, --notes\\n   - Only update provided fields, update updated_at\\n   - Error if not found\\n6. Implement 'rm' command:\\n   - Arg: name (required), --force flag\\n   - If has contacts or deals and no --force, error with message\\n   - With --force, cascade delete related records\\n7. Register company app in main.py via app.add_typer()\",\n      \"passes\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"pending\",\n      \"failure_reason\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"run_id\": 2,\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"Build contact commands: add, list, show, edit, rm\",\n      \"steps\": \"1. Create crm/src/crm/commands/contact.py with typer app\\n2. Implement 'add' command:\\n   - Args: name (required), --company (resolve to company_id by name), --email, --phone, --role, --tags, --notes\\n   - Company is optional (independent contacts ok per spec)\\n   - If --company given but not found, error exit code 3\\n   - Insert into contacts, emit success\\n3. Implement 'list' command:\\n   - Optional --company filter (resolve name to id), --tag filter\\n   - Tag filter: match against comma-separated tags field\\n   - Return array of contacts with company name joined\\n   - Text format: rich table with ID, Name, Company, Role, Email\\n4. Implement 'show' command:\\n   - Arg: name, look up by name\\n   - Include company name (joined), recent interactions count\\n   - Error if not found\\n5. Implement 'edit' command:\\n   - Arg: name, optional --name, --company, --email, --phone, --role, --tags, --notes\\n   - Resolve --company to company_id\\n   - Only update provided fields\\n6. Implement 'rm' command:\\n   - Arg: name, delete contact and related interactions\\n7. Register contact app in main.py via app.add_typer()\",\n      \"passes\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"pending\",\n      \"failure_reason\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"run_id\": 2,\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"Build interaction logging commands: call, email, meeting, note\",\n      \"steps\": \"1. Create crm/src/crm/commands/log.py with typer app\\n2. All 4 subcommands (call, email, meeting, note) share same structure:\\n   - Arg: contact_name (required), --summary (required)\\n   - Optional: --followup (Nd/Nw/YYYY-MM-DD), --followup-note, --date (defaults to now)\\n   - The interaction type is set by which subcommand is called\\n3. Implement followup date parsing:\\n   - '7d' -> today + 7 days\\n   - '2w' -> today + 14 days\\n   - 'YYYY-MM-DD' -> exact date\\n   - Invalid format -> error exit code 2\\n4. Resolve contact by name, auto-resolve company_id from contact's company\\n5. Insert into interactions table with all fields\\n6. Emit success with full interaction data including contact name and company name\\n7. Text format: confirmation message with followup date if set\\n8. Register log app in main.py via app.add_typer()\",\n      \"passes\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"pending\",\n      \"failure_reason\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 11,\n      \"run_id\": 2,\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"Build deal commands: add, list, show, move, rm\",\n      \"steps\": \"1. Create crm/src/crm/commands/deal.py with typer app\\n2. Implement 'add' command:\\n   - Args: title (required), --company (required, resolve to id), --value, --stage (default 'lead'), --contact (optional, resolve to id), --notes\\n   - Validate stage is one of: lead/proposal/negotiation/active/closed-won/closed-lost\\n   - Error if company not found (exit 3)\\n   - Insert into deals, emit success\\n3. Implement 'list' command:\\n   - Optional --stage filter, --company filter\\n   - Return deals with company name and contact name joined\\n   - Text format: rich table with ID, Title, Company, Value, Stage\\n4. Implement 'show' command:\\n   - Arg: title, look up by title\\n   - Include company name, contact name\\n5. Implement 'move' command:\\n   - Arg: title, --stage (required)\\n   - Validate stage, update stage and updated_at\\n   - Emit success with updated deal\\n6. Implement 'rm' command:\\n   - Arg: title, delete deal\\n7. Register deal app in main.py via app.add_typer()\",\n      \"passes\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"pending\",\n      \"failure_reason\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 12,\n      \"run_id\": 2,\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"Build followup commands: list (default/--week/--all) and done\",\n      \"steps\": \"1. Create crm/src/crm/commands/followup.py with typer app\\n2. Implement default 'followups' command (list):\\n   - Default: show interactions where followup_date <= today (due + overdue)\\n   - --week flag: followup_date <= today + 7 days\\n   - --all flag: all where followup_date IS NOT NULL\\n   - Join with contacts and companies for display\\n   - Return array with interaction id, contact name, company, summary, followup_date, followup_note, days_overdue\\n   - Text format: rich table sorted by date, with color coding for overdue\\n3. Implement 'done' subcommand:\\n   - Arg: interaction id (integer)\\n   - Set followup_date and followup_note to NULL\\n   - Error if id not found\\n   - Emit success\\n4. Register followup app in main.py\",\n      \"passes\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"pending\",\n      \"failure_reason\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 13,\n      \"run_id\": 2,\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"Build search and status commands\",\n      \"steps\": \"1. Create crm/src/crm/commands/search.py:\\n   - Arg: query (required string)\\n   - Search across all 4 tables using LIKE on text columns:\\n     - companies: name, industry, notes\\n     - contacts: name, email, role, tags, notes\\n     - interactions: summary, followup_note\\n     - deals: title, notes\\n   - Return grouped results: {companies: [...], contacts: [...], interactions: [...], deals: [...]}\\n   - Text format: sections with rich tables for each entity type that has matches\\n   - Register as app.command() directly on main app (not subcommand group)\\n2. Create crm/src/crm/commands/status.py:\\n   - No arguments, dashboard summary\\n   - Query and return:\\n     - active_deals: count and total value of deals with stage 'active'\\n     - pipeline_deals: count and total value of non-closed deals\\n     - overdue_followups: count where followup_date < today\\n     - upcoming_followups: count where followup_date between today and today+7\\n     - recent_interactions: last 5 interactions with contact/company names\\n     - company_counts: dict of status -> count\\n   - Text format: rich panel with formatted summary\\n   - Register as app.command() on main app\\n3. Register both in main.py\",\n      \"passes\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"pending\",\n      \"failure_reason\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 14,\n      \"run_id\": 2,\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"Write tests for all modules using pytest + CliRunner\",\n      \"steps\": \"1. Create crm/tests/conftest.py:\\n   - Fixture: tmp_db that patches get_db_path to use a temp file\\n   - Fixture: runner using typer.testing.CliRunner\\n   - Fixture: seeded_db that inserts sample company, contact, interaction, deal\\n2. Create crm/tests/test_db.py:\\n   - Test init_db creates all tables\\n   - Test schema has correct columns\\n   - Test foreign key enforcement\\n3. Create crm/tests/test_company.py:\\n   - Test add, list, show, edit, rm\\n   - Test duplicate name error\\n   - Test rm with --force and without when has contacts\\n   - Test list with --status filter\\n4. Create crm/tests/test_contact.py:\\n   - Test add with and without company\\n   - Test list with --company and --tag filters\\n   - Test show, edit, rm\\n   - Test add with nonexistent company\\n5. Create crm/tests/test_log.py:\\n   - Test all 4 interaction types (call, email, meeting, note)\\n   - Test followup date parsing (Nd, Nw, YYYY-MM-DD)\\n   - Test --date override\\n   - Test auto company_id resolution\\n6. Create crm/tests/test_deal.py:\\n   - Test add, list, show, move, rm\\n   - Test stage validation\\n   - Test list with --stage and --company filters\\n7. Create crm/tests/test_followup.py:\\n   - Test default (due today + overdue)\\n   - Test --week and --all\\n   - Test done command clears followup\\n8. Run pytest and verify all tests pass\\n9. Install package with pip install -e . and verify crm --help works\",\n      \"passes\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"pending\",\n      \"failure_reason\": null\n    }\n  ],\n  \"count\": 8\n}","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Cyg4QKCyUeEmjkKVA3Vuih"}
