{"session_id":"7f422c6a-05c8-4182-82e2-fa44f1469a5f","transcript_path":"/home/blgroce/.claude/projects/-home-blgroce-tools-cli-tools/7f422c6a-05c8-4182-82e2-fa44f1469a5f.jsonl","cwd":"/home/blgroce/tools/cli-tools","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","tool_name":"Task","tool_input":{"description":"Explore describe-image patterns","prompt":"Quick exploration: Read the following files from the describe-image tool to understand patterns for output helpers and main.py structure:\n1. /home/blgroce/tools/cli-tools/describe-image/src/describe_image/main.py - look at how --format and --quiet are handled as global options, how output settings are stored in ctx.obj\n2. Any output.py or similar helper file in describe-image that handles emit_success/emit_error\n\nReturn the full content of both files so I can see the patterns.","subagent_type":"Explore"},"tool_response":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Quick exploration: Read the following files from the describe-image tool to understand patterns for output helpers and main.py structure:\n1. /home/blgroce/tools/cli-tools/describe-image/src/describe_image/main.py - look at how --format and --quiet are handled as global options, how output settings are stored in ctx.obj\n2. Any output.py or similar helper file in describe-image that handles emit_success/emit_error\n\nReturn the full content of both files so I can see the patterns.","agentId":"a383355","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Here are the key patterns from the describe-image tool:\n\n## Pattern Summary\n\n### 1. **OutputSettings Dataclass** (lines 45-48)\n```python\n@dataclass\nclass OutputSettings:\n    format: str\n    quiet: bool\n```\nSimple dataclass to store output preferences globally via `ctx.obj`.\n\n### 2. **emit_success() Function** (lines 51-58)\n```python\ndef emit_success(data: Any, settings: OutputSettings, text: Optional[str] = None) -> None:\n    if settings.quiet:\n        raise typer.Exit(ExitCode.SUCCESS)\n    if settings.format == \"text\":\n        print(text or \"\")\n        raise typer.Exit(ExitCode.SUCCESS)\n    print(json.dumps({\"success\": True, \"data\": data}))\n    raise typer.Exit(ExitCode.SUCCESS)\n```\n- Respects `--quiet` flag (suppress output)\n- Respects `--format` flag (text vs JSON)\n- Provides optional `text` parameter for human-readable output\n- Always exits explicitly with proper exit code\n\n### 3. **emit_error() Function** (lines 61-71)\n```python\ndef emit_error(\n    message: str,\n    settings: OutputSettings,\n    code: str = \"ERROR\",\n    exit_code: ExitCode = ExitCode.GENERAL_ERROR,\n) -> None:\n    if settings.format == \"text\":\n        print(f\"{code}: {message}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        raise typer.Exit(exit_code)\n    print(json.dumps({\"error\": True, \"code\": code, \"message\": message}), file=sys.stderr)\n    raise typer.Exit(exit_code)\n```\n- Always writes to stderr\n- Takes a `code` parameter for machine-readable error classification\n- Takes `exit_code` parameter for proper exit codes\n\n### 4. **get_settings() Helper** (lines 74-77)\n```python\ndef get_settings(ctx: typer.Context) -> OutputSettings:\n    if isinstance(ctx.obj, OutputSettings):\n        return ctx.obj\n    return OutputSettings(format=\"json\", quiet=False)\n```\nSafe way to retrieve settings from context in subcommands.\n\n### 5. **Global Options via @app.callback()** (lines 86-107)\n```python\n@app.callback()\ndef main(\n    ctx: typer.Context,\n    format: str = typer.Option(\"json\", \"--format\", help=\"Output format: json or text\"),\n    quiet: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--quiet\", \"-q\", help=\"Suppress non-error output\"),\n    version: bool = typer.Option(...),\n) -> None:\n    # Validate format\n    if format not in {\"json\", \"text\"}:\n        # ... error handling ...\n    ctx.obj = OutputSettings(format=format, quiet=quiet)\n```\n- Callback runs before any command\n- Sets `ctx.obj` to share settings with all subcommands\n- Validates format option early\n\n### 6. **ExitCode Enum** (lines 37-42)\n```python\nclass ExitCode(IntEnum):\n    SUCCESS = 0\n    GENERAL_ERROR = 1\n    INVALID_ARGS = 2\n    NOT_FOUND = 3\n    EXTERNAL_FAILURE = 4\n```\nStandard exit codes per CLAUDE.md spec.\n\n### 7. **No Separate output.py File**\nThere's no separate output helper file in describe-image—all helper functions are inline in `main.py`, which is a valid approach for simpler tools.\n\nThis is the pattern you should replicate in other tools!"}],"totalDurationMs":10437,"totalTokens":18197,"totalToolUseCount":2,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5476,"cache_read_input_tokens":11831,"output_tokens":883,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5476,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BebjsHFZEc4rZmA5ET64C5"}
