{"session_id":"d51db129-79f5-43a1-9db8-46f176b65840","transcript_path":"/home/blgroce/.claude/projects/-home-blgroce-tools-cli-tools/d51db129-79f5-43a1-9db8-46f176b65840.jsonl","cwd":"/home/blgroce/tools/cli-tools","permission_mode":"bypassPermissions","hook_event_name":"PostToolUse","tool_name":"Bash","tool_input":{"command":"python3 .claude/skills/project-context/scripts/task_list.py --run-id 2 --pending","description":"Get pending tasks for run 2"},"tool_response":{"stdout":"{\n  \"tasks\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": 8,\n      \"run_id\": 2,\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"Build company commands: add, list, show, edit, rm\",\n      \"steps\": \"1. Create crm/src/crm/commands/company.py with typer app\\n2. Implement 'add' command:\\n   - Args: name (required), --status, --industry, --website, --notes\\n   - Insert into companies table, emit success with company data\\n   - Handle duplicate name (unique constraint) with proper error\\n3. Implement 'list' command:\\n   - Optional --status filter\\n   - Return array of companies as JSON\\n   - Text format: rich table with columns: ID, Name, Industry, Status\\n4. Implement 'show' command:\\n   - Arg: name (required), look up by name\\n   - Include related contacts count and deals count in output\\n   - Error if not found (exit code 3)\\n5. Implement 'edit' command:\\n   - Arg: name (required), optional --name, --status, --industry, --website, --notes\\n   - Only update provided fields, update updated_at\\n   - Error if not found\\n6. Implement 'rm' command:\\n   - Arg: name (required), --force flag\\n   - If has contacts or deals and no --force, error with message\\n   - With --force, cascade delete related records\\n7. Register company app in main.py via app.add_typer()\",\n      \"passes\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"pending\",\n      \"failure_reason\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 9,\n      \"run_id\": 2,\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"Build contact commands: add, list, show, edit, rm\",\n      \"steps\": \"1. Create crm/src/crm/commands/contact.py with typer app\\n2. Implement 'add' command:\\n   - Args: name (required), --company (resolve to company_id by name), --email, --phone, --role, --tags, --notes\\n   - Company is optional (independent contacts ok per spec)\\n   - If --company given but not found, error exit code 3\\n   - Insert into contacts, emit success\\n3. Implement 'list' command:\\n   - Optional --company filter (resolve name to id), --tag filter\\n   - Tag filter: match against comma-separated tags field\\n   - Return array of contacts with company name joined\\n   - Text format: rich table with ID, Name, Company, Role, Email\\n4. Implement 'show' command:\\n   - Arg: name, look up by name\\n   - Include company name (joined), recent interactions count\\n   - Error if not found\\n5. Implement 'edit' command:\\n   - Arg: name, optional --name, --company, --email, --phone, --role, --tags, --notes\\n   - Resolve --company to company_id\\n   - Only update provided fields\\n6. Implement 'rm' command:\\n   - Arg: name, delete contact and related interactions\\n7. Register contact app in main.py via app.add_typer()\",\n      \"passes\": 0,\n      \"status\": \"pending\",\n      \"failure_reason\": null\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": 10,\n      \"run_id\": 2,\n      \"category\": \"feature\",\n      \"description\": \"Build interaction logging commands: call, email, meeting, note\",\n      \"steps\": \"1. Create crm/src/crm/commands/log.py with typer app\\n2. All 4 subcommands (call, email, meeting, note) share same structure:\\n   - Arg: contact_name (required), --summary (required)\\n   - Optional: --followup (Nd/Nw/YYYY-MM-DD), --followup-note, --date (defaults to now)\\n   - The interaction type is set by which subcommand is called\\n3. Implement followup date parsing:\\n   - '7d' -> today + 7 days\\n   - '2w' -> today + 14 days\\n   - 'YYYY-MM-DD' -> exact date\\n   - Invalid format -> error exit code 2\\n